 <i>lastly, Sheila Levitt.</i>

00:16:34.822 --> 00:16:37.756 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Shokichi) These eleven brave</i>
 <i>souls sacrificed their lives,</i>

00:16:37.789 --> 00:16:42.222 position:13% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Shokichi) in the hope of</i>
 <i>finding salvation for those</i>
 <i>depending on us back on Earth.</i>

00:16:42.255 --> 00:16:44.656 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Shokichi) We will return their</i>
 <i>remains home.</i>

00:16:45.589 --> 00:16:47.155 position:27% line:89% align:start
No matter what.

00:16:47.656 --> 00:16:50.722 position:16% line:83% align:start
Eleven of us died today.
Remember them.

00:16:53.088 --> 00:16:57.155 position:13% line:83% align:start
The situation is far more
critical than we ever imagined.

00:16:57.522 --> 00:17:03.589 position:7% line:71% align:start
 <i>(Shokichi) After entering the</i>
 <i>atmosphere, we were ambushed.</i>
 <i>They infiltrated our ship and</i>
 <i>destroyed our main engine.</i>

00:17:03.622 --> 00:17:09.255 position:10% line:71% align:start
 <i>(Shokichi) We had to execute</i>
 <i>Plan Delta. We boarded the six</i>
 <i>escape vessels and landed</i>
 <i>separately on Mars.</i>

00:17:09.289 --> 00:17:11.523 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Michelle) And received one hell</i>
 <i>of a warm welcome.</i>

00:17:11.557 --> 00:17:15.690 position:5% line:77% align:start
It's safe to assume the
remaining squads came under
attack as well.

00:17:15.723 --> 00:17:20.557 position:13% line:77% align:start
Only squad five contacted us,
reporting that squad four had
been wiped out.

00:17:20.590 --> 00:17:24.189 position:10% line:83% align:start
Other than that, we received a
single SOS from squad six.

00:17:24.523 --> 00:17:27.223 position:24% line:83% align:start
We haven't heard anything
from the other squads.

00:17:27.490 --> 00:17:29.256 position:19% line:89% align:start
You gotta be kidding.

00:17:29.290 --> 00:17:31.490 position:5% line:83% align:start
That doesn't make sense. They're
all dead?

00:17:34.089 --> 00:17:38.456 position:5% line:77% align:start
Um, maybe they're waiting for us
at the rendezvous point! I bet
they're all fine.

00:17:39.024 --> 00:17:42.723 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's just a coincidence. We
can't give up!

00:17:42.757 --> 00:17:45.557 position:7% line:83% align:start
And on the bright side, we got
plenty of samples,

00:17:45.590 --> 00:17:50.657 position:10% line:77% align:start
so let's all cheer up and head
toward Annex 1 where the rest of
the crew is waiting for us!

00:17:50.690 --> 00:17:53.557 position:13% line:83% align:start
Or, um, whatever you think we
should do, Captain.

00:17:53.590 --> 00:17:56.657 position:5% line:83% align:start
No, you're completely right,
Yaeko.

00:17:56.690 --> 00:17:59.857 position:5% line:83% align:start
Come! Let's all
head back to the main ship.

00:18:00.089 --> 00:18:03.890 position:5% line:77% align:start
Since our ride here can't fly,
we'll be on the road for about a
week.

00:18:04.223 --> 00:18:05.323 position:75% line:89% align:start
A week?

00:18:05.356 --> 00:18:07.189 position:13% line:89% align:start
We're almost out of serum.

00:18:09.056 --> 00:18:10.990 position:16% line:89% align:start
Time for some shut eye.

00:18:11.024 --> 00:18:12.290 position:33% line:89% align:start
(All) What?

00:18:13.490 --> 00:18:16.124 position:5% line:83% align:start
What? Were you really planning
on staying up the whole week?

00:18:16.157 --> 00:18:17.124 position:38% line:89% align:start
No, but.

00:18:17.157 --> 00:18:20.591 position:5% line:83% align:start
Just relax. You guys have all
been through hell.

00:18:20.624 --> 00:18:25.324 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Michelle) You're alive. And in</i>
 <i>order to stay that way you need</i>
 <i>to eat and rest.</i>

00:18:25.357 --> 00:18:29.691 position:5% line:77% align:start
I understand you may be worried
about the others. This is a
battlefield, after all.

00:18:29.724 --> 00:18:32.124 position:5% line:83% align:start
Being human is nothing to be
ashamed of...

00:18:32.157 --> 00:18:35.991 position:13% line:5% align:start
 <i>She's grown up a lot since I</i>
 <i>first recruited her at 21.</i>

00:18:36.025 --> 00:18:40.991 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>Maybe being a leader does that</i>
 <i>to a person. Or maybe it's</i>
 <i>because of her new comrades.</i>

00:18:41.025 --> 00:18:47.090 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>[Chuckles] Either way, I won't</i>
 <i>mention that your rousing little</i>
 <i>speech "borrowed" heavily from</i>
 <i>my own.</i>

00:18:47.124 --> 00:18:49.391 position:5% line:83% align:start
All right ladies. If you need to
shower, follow me.

00:18:49.424 --> 00:18:50.558 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Amelia) Ooh! Count me in!</i>

00:18:50.591 --> 00:18:51.958 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Shokichi) Be careful. </i>

00:18:53.090 --> 00:18:54.457 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Michelle) Copy that. Bring some</i>
 <i>serum just in case.</i>

00:18:54.491 --> 00:18:55.524 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Kanako) Can do!</i>

00:18:56.057 --> 00:19:07.157 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Giggling/Talking]

00:19:07.190 --> 00:19:08.424 position:44% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:19:08.991 --> 00:19:10.891 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Groans]

00:19:10.925 --> 00:19:13.424 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Shokichi) Hey. Hey!</i>

00:19:13.457 --> 00:19:16.057 position:35% line:83% align:start
